  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers just flipped into short gamma BREAKOUT regime with massive negative GEX at 6550 creating a dangerous amplification zone right below current spot (6553) - they're forced to buy any dips toward 6550 and sell rallies toward 6580, creating whipsaw action in this narrow 30-point range. The proximity to max negative gamma at 6550 means any downside breach will trigger accelerated dealer buying that could spark violent snapback moves, while the massive positive gamma wall at 6580 acts as magnetic resistance where dealers turn into heavy sellers.\n\nWatch 6550 as the critical amplification trigger - break below ignites dealer buying panic, while 6580 becomes the key distribution level where dealer selling pressure intensifies.",
